A father and son who were in the Morrisons store in Hagley Road, Edgbaston, Birmingham, spotted Smith as he sat in the back of a police car.

The father, who would not be named, said: 'As we pulled into the car park we saw shop workers running out of the store after someone.

'Two baskets of wine were outside the door.

'We were told by someone at the checkout that it was Danny from Benefits Street.

'We watched the show so we knew who he was.'

He featured heavily in the first episode of Channel 4’s Benefits Street, which was filmed in Winson Green’s James Turner Street.

